We walked here after the monument lighting (busy time, I get it) last year and stood in the lobby for 10 minutes while every server who walked by ignored our increasingly flabbergasted attempts to get their attention. While we were standing there, a group of six women walked past us straight up to a server who readily took them over to a table. This same server had ignored us several times, though we were standing right next to the register she twice accessed (as fast as she could). I understand this was a busy time, but we weren't talked to by a single staff member - not even a "we'll be right with you" - and felt like freaking ghosts. They've consistently seemed short-staffed in the past, and over the last year or two have also seemed short-pleasant staffed. I just can't imagine ever sitting to eat here again after this experience and I highly recommend avoiding this place during busy times.

Good news: As of early 2018, this is sort of *THE* place from which to get vegan pizza delivered in the city. They have decent non-dairy cheese, plenty of veggie options and even meatless pepperoni. (Don't roll your eyes, meat eaters -- it's pretty good stuff.)  Bad news: two things. First, they aren't great at keeping the vegan options stocked. More often than not, I'll put in an order online only to be called 15 minutes later to be told that they don't have either vegan cheese or vegan pepperoni stocked (or both). This is related to the second issue: delivery *always* takes too long. They shortest I've ever been quoted is 45 minutes, and regardless of how long the quote is, you can expect to add 20-40 minutes before you get your pizza.
